ger which the state believes they’ve put themselves by attending a gathering exceeding 20 persons, they must agree to go on 14 days isolation to protect other members of the public from any likely danger. Vanguard News Nigeria. The Lagos State Government has withdrawn charges against Naira Marley, Babatunde Gbadamosi, and his wife Folashade. The State Government gave conditions for withdrawing the charge for flouting the state Coronavirus social distancing directive brought against the defendants. Naira Marley was represented in court by Damilola Ayinde-Marshall alongside Afeez Olabisi while… April 8, 2020 In "News" By Henry Ojelu The Lagos State Government today gave reasons and conditions for withdrawing the charge brought against controversial hip-hop star, Azeez Fashola popularly known as Naira Marley, former Lagos governorship aspirant, Babatunde Gbadamosi and his wife Folashade for flouting the state Coronavirus social distancing directive. Naira Marley was represented… April 8, 2020 In "News" In spite of the lockdown still in place, dozens of fans of singer, Azeez Fashola, aka Naira Marley, were at the premises of an Ikeja Chief Magistrates’ Court to show support for their idol, the News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports. April 8, 2020 In "News"